# Firebase patterns

## Database

This app uses **Firebase Realtime Database**, not Firestore. Data model:

```
rooms/{roomId}/
  answers/{cardId}/  → { answer, question, type?, answeredAt }
  skipped/{cardId}/  → true
```

## Security rules (`database.rules.json`)

- Read/write requires `auth != null` (anonymous auth satisfies this)
- `answers` entries must include string `answer` and `question`; optional `type` string
- `skipped` entries must be boolean `true`

Before deploying rule changes, test with emulators and consider the `firebase-security-rules-auditor` skill.

## Emulators (`firebase.json`)

| Service | Port |
|---------|------|
| Auth    | 9099 |
| RTDB    | 9000 |
| Hosting | 5000 |

`firebase-init.js` connects to emulators when hostname is `localhost` or `127.0.0.1`.

## Deploy

- Live hosting: auto-deploy via GitHub Actions on merge to `main`
- Manual: `firebase deploy --only hosting,database`
- Project ID: `relationships-d7fce` (see `.firebaserc`)

## CLI version

Always use latest Firebase CLI: `npx -y firebase-tools@latest --version`
